cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on speech recognition and synthesis, which falls under the domain of sound processing. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper involves learning representations of speech utterances that are phoneme-synchronized and phonetically clustered, which are related to language processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a Sequential Representation Quantization AutoEncoder (SeqRQ-AE) to learn from primarily unpaired audio data, which is a machine learning technique. 
- cs.SI (Speech and Audio Processing): The paper deals with speech recognition and synthesis, which are subfields of speech and audio processing.
